race.comment: CRASHMYPLAYA (7) finally drawn a low gate after turning in a slashing performance when coming from near last on the turn with a game second over 1509m at this track. Gets a solid tempo again and can race closer from the draw. Hard to hold out. TALK ABOUT LAYLA (4) covered plenty of ground in the run when loomed ominously for a respectable third over 1400m at Taree in a Super Maiden. Near her top and shapes as a top-three player. SARA'S ROCKET (3) had mixed luck in two career starts and the winkers go on for the first time today. Covered ground in the run when a plugging fifth over 1250m at Newcastle. Can show a bit more here with Ash Morgan booked. TEMPLE BELLS (9) smart return when closed strongly for a narrow second in the small field at Coffs Harbour over 1215m. Extra trip in her favour and the claim helps again.
